    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How long does each take to work?</summary>
      <p>Ashwagandha: measurable cortisol reduction in 2-4 weeks, full stress and sleep benefits by 6-8 weeks. Lion's mane: subtle focus improvements in 2-4 weeks, significant cognitive benefits documented at 8-16 weeks. Neither produces immediate acute effects. Consistency is critical for both.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What are KSM-66 and Sensoril?</summary>
      <p>KSM-66 is a full-spectrum ashwagandha root extract standardized to 5% withanolides, used in over 24 clinical trials. It is the most versatile extract. Sensoril is a root + leaf extract standardized to 10% withanolides, particularly studied for cortisol reduction. Both are superior to generic unstandardized ashwagandha powders. Always check which extract your gummy contains.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are there any side effects of taking both?</summary>
      <p>Both have excellent safety profiles. Ashwagandha: avoid with hyperthyroidism, autoimmune conditions, or during pregnancy. Lion's mane: avoid with mushroom allergies. Both may interact with blood sugar and blood-thinning medications. No known interactions between the two compounds exist. Consult your physician if taking medications.</p>
    </details>

